      "valid_scope": "section_pair",
      "why_conflicting": "Authentication section specifies sessions expire after 48 hours of inactivity, while Session Retention Policy mandates sessions must be kept active for a minimum of 30 days and must not be terminated before that window elapses. These are directly contradictory termination conditions.",
      "why_llm_cannot_decide": "Both rules are stated as mandatory requirements. The Purpose and Core Concept do not establish a precedence rule between operational session expiry and compliance-driven retention obligations. It is unclear whether 'session record retention' and 'active session' refer to the same object or different artifacts (live session token vs. audit log row), which is a domain/architecture decision requiring human clarification."
    },
    {
      "base_source_hashes": [
        {
          "hash": "d4eb3e64eb3f7967f68aa03b573494928d5b35d426155a3141a8f735770e5932",
          "source_ref": "docs/spec/sample.md#0005-session-retention-policy"
