      "valid_scope": "section_pair",
      "why_conflicting": "Session Termination mandates automatic purge of sessions after 24 hours of inactivity, while Session Retention Policy prohibits terminating any session before a 30-day retention window — these two rules are mutually exclusive for inactive sessions.",
      "why_llm_cannot_decide": "Both rules are stated as hard requirements with no exception clause. Purpose and Core Concept describe this spec as a fixture designed to avoid triggering LLM conflict detection, yet the texts directly contradict each other on session lifetime. Whether the retention policy creates an exception to the inactivity purge, or whether the purge applies only to in-memory state while the record persists, cannot be inferred from the text alone — that distinction requires human authorial intent."
    },
