          "left_excerpt": "A successful login establishes a session that expires after 48 hours of inactivity.",
          "right_excerpt": "Sessions that exceed the 24-hour inactivity window are automatically purged by a background sweep that runs every five minutes.",
          "severity": "high",
          "why_conflicting": "Authentication sets the inactivity expiry at 48 hours; Session Termination sets it at 24 hours. A session inactive for 25–48 hours would be purged under Session Termination rules but still considered valid under Authentication rules."
        }
      ],
      "created_at": "1970-01-01T00:00:00Z",
      "recommended_next_action": "Decide the single authoritative inactivity timeout and update both sections to agree. If the two values are intentional (e.g., 48h for soft expiry vs. 24h for hard purge), document the distinction explicitly in both sections.",
